[2] Florida
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2021
Source: EquiManagement [edited]
https://equimanagement.com/news/equine-neurologic-herpesvirus-confirmed-in-duval-county-florida


The Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services confirmed one case of equine herpesvirus at a boarding facility in Duval County. Another horse on the premises is positive for EHV-1 but had no neurologic signs at the time of this report.

A single horse with neurological signs was reported by a private veterinary practitioner in Duval County on 28 Mar 2021. Test results completed 30 Mar [2021] were positive for equine herpesvirus type 1 (EHV-1). The horse is currently being treated at a separate isolation facility.

A 2nd febrile horse on the premises has tested positive for EHV-1, but currently has no neurologic signs.

The Division of Animal Industry has placed a quarantine on the premises, and an investigation is ongoing. There is no known epidemiological link between the horses on the Duval County premises and the positive EHV-1 cases reported in early March [2021] in Marion County.

Visit <www.FDACS.gov/ai> for additional information.

Information for this report was provided by the Equine Disease Communication Center.

[Byline: Kimberly S. Brown]

